rgy and women, positioning lay Catholic women as central actors in the making of modern Ireland.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCatholic womenxReligious lifezIreland. 0aCatholic womenzIrelandxHistory. 0aCatholic womenzIrelandxSocial conditions. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Catholic.2bisacsh  aCatholic Church.  aCatholicism.  aIreland.  aVirgin Mary.  adevotion.  afamily.  agirls.  alaity.  amothers.  apopular devotion.  areligion.  awomen.1 aDelay, Cara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packagez978311128249740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613640440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526136404423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526136404/original  a978-3-11-128249-7  Manchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packageb2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles